.SH NAME
TextDecoder.fatal \- TextDecoder: fatal property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]fatal\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]TextDecoder\f[R] interface is a \f[CR]Boolean\f[R] indicating
whether the error mode is fatal.
.PP
If the property is \f[CR]true\f[R], then a decoder will throw a
\f[CR]TypeError\f[R] if it encounters malformed data while decoding.
If \f[CR]false\f[R], the decoder will substitute the invalid data with
the replacement character \f[CR]U+FFFD\f[R] (ï¿½).
The value of the property is set in the \f[CR]TextDecoder()\f[R]
constructor.
.SH VALUE
A boolean which will be \f[CR]true\f[R] if the error mode is set to
\f[CR]fatal\f[R].
Otherwise, it will be \f[CR]false\f[R], indicating that the error mode
is \f[CR]replacement\f[R].
